<h4>Viewing Options for a Window</h4>

					    

<p>In looking for data stored in files and folders in the C: drive or other
					    drives on your computer, you can choose to look at the information you see
					    in a window in different layouts.</p>
					
					    <p>The choices you have for viewing differ a little depending on the
					    version of Windows you have on your computer. The <strong>view choices</strong> are:
					    <strong>thumbnails, tiles, icons (extra large, large, medium, small), list,
					    and details</strong>. Because there are so many of these, if you want to
					    see what these look like before trying them on your computer, the Online
					    Demo can show you.</p>
					
					    <p>You can see file sizes and other information when the <strong>Details</strong> option is
					    selected.</p>
					
					    <p>Search the window to determine where the viewing options are located for
					    your version of Windows, by using the following hints as to where to
					    look:</p><br>
					
