<h4>Folder Option Box for Windows 7, Windows Vista, and Classic Windows</h4>
				
				        <p>Once you have located the Folder Options Box, to change the way the
				        file extension is viewed:</p>
				
				        <ol>
				            <li>Make sure the <strong>View Tab</strong> is selected.</li>
				
				            <li><strong>Uncheck</strong> the box by Hide extensions for
				            known file types so that you can see the file extension.</li>
				
				            <li>Apply this view setting to all folders by clicking on the
				            <strong>"Apply to Folders" button</strong>.</li>
				
				            <li>After you have clicked on the Apply to Folders button, the
				            Folder Options window should close and disappear from view. If it
				            does not, click on the Ok button in the bottom of the Folder
				            Options window.</li>
				        </ol>
				        
				        <img class="space" src="images/filesandfolders/folderoptionsviewtab.jpg">
				
				        <p>The file extensions will show with this setting.</p>
