<a name="ss3"></a>	

<h4>Controlling the Number of Windows That are Viewed</h4>



					        <p>The Windows program either opens up a <strong>new </strong>window for viewing
					        information each time you double click on a folder or it <strong>reuses</strong> the
					        same window. As an empowered user, it is your choice.</p>
					
					        <p>Please note, this is different from starting a window with the Start
					        Button. Every time you go to the Start Button, you create a new window
					        no matter what settings you choose.</p>
					
					        <p>But once a window is opened, you can choose either to create a new
					        one each time you double click on an item inside that window or you can
					        choose to have Windows open up the item within the same window.</p>
					
					        <p>To make your choice about this setting, let's again explore the
					        Control Panel and Folder Options. If you do not have access to the
					        Control Panel, do not worry. You will have to use the folder settings
					        and options that are already set.</p>
					
					        <p>Once you find the Folder Options Box:</p>
					
					        <ol>
					            <li>Make sure the <strong>General Tab</strong> is selected.</li>
					
					            <li>Click the button by <strong>Open each folder in the same
					            window</strong> or <strong>Open each folder in its own
					            window</strong>.</li>
					        </ol>
					        

<img class="img-wrap style1" src="images/filesandfolders/folderoptionsgeneraltab.jpg">
